@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{register-extras.el} extends the built-in Emacs register system (@samp{register.el}) with additional storage operations and a unified transient menu. Emacs registers are single-character slots that can hold text, numbers, positions, window configurations, and more, but the standard commands are scattered and easy to forget. This package adds:

@itemize
@item
A command to store text directly from the kill ring into a register (@ref{Kill ring to register}).
@item
A lightweight buffer-register system for quick switching between buffers by single-character keys (@ref{Buffer registers}).
@item
A transient dispatch menu that groups all register operations in one place (@ref{Transient menu}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{register} and @samp{transient}.

