@node Kill ring to register
@section Kill ring to register

@findex register-extras-kill-to-register
The built-in @code{copy-to-register} stores the current region, but sometimes you want to store a previously killed piece of text without first yanking and re-selecting it. The command @code{register-extras-kill-to-register} prompts you to choose an item from the kill ring (via @code{read-from-kill-ring}) and then a target register (via @code{register-read-with-preview}), and stores the chosen text in that register with @code{set-register}. This saves the round-trip of yanking, selecting, and copying to a register.

@node Buffer registers
@section Buffer registers

@findex register-extras-buffer-to-register
@findex register-extras-jump-to-buffer
While Emacs registers can store buffer positions, there is no built-in way to bind a single character to a buffer for instant switching. The command @code{register-extras-buffer-to-register} prompts for a character and associates it with the current buffer in an internal alist (@code{register-extras-keys-alist}). Any previous association for that character is replaced.

The companion command @code{register-extras-jump-to-buffer} prompts for a character and switches to the buffer associated with it. If the buffer has been killed since the association was made, a message is displayed instead.

These two commands provide a lightweight alternative to bookmarks or tab-bar tabs when you want to toggle rapidly between a small set of buffers during a focused work session.

@node Transient menu
@section Transient menu

@findex register-extras-dispatch
The command @code{register-extras-dispatch} presents a transient menu that organizes all register-related operations by content type. The menu groups include:

@itemize
@item
@strong{region}: append, copy, and prepend to register.
@item
@strong{number}: store and increment.
@item
@strong{kill ring}: store via @code{register-extras-kill-to-register} (@ref{Kill ring to register}).
@item
@strong{kmacro}: store and execute.
@item
@strong{rectangle}: copy to register.
@item
@strong{window/frame config}: store frame, window, or all-windows configuration.
@item
@strong{navigation}: jump to register and store point.
@item
@strong{buffer}: jump and store via the buffer-register commands (@ref{Buffer registers}).
@item
@strong{display}: consult (via @samp{consult-register}), list, and view registers.
@item
@strong{insert}: insert register contents.
@end itemize

This menu provides a single entry point for the full range of register operations, removing the need to remember individual key bindings for each command.

